---
const sections = [
  {
    title: 'Why Are UK Households Switching to IPTV?',
    body: "The maths are hard to argue with. A standard cable or satellite package costs £50 to £100 a month. A UK IPTV subscription from UKIPTVBOX starts at £14.99 and covers more channels and more on-demand content than most cable packages, on every device you already own. UK viewers are switching because broadband speeds have reached the point where a live 4K stream is indistinguishable from satellite, without the dish.",
  },
  {
    title: 'How Does UKIPTVBOX Work?',
    body: "Order your UK IPTV subscription via WhatsApp and your login credentials arrive within minutes. Open the app on your device (Smart TV, Firestick, Android, iOS, MAG, Formuler, Nvidia Shield, Apple TV, Windows, Mac or Enigma2), enter your details, and you are watching live channels in 4K within five minutes of subscribing. Everything runs through UKIPTVBOX's dedicated UK and EU servers, load-balanced for 99.9% uptime.",
  },
  {
    title: 'Is IPTV Legal in the UK?',
    body: 'IPTV as a delivery technology is entirely legal. The BBC, Sky, Netflix and every major UK broadcaster use it to deliver content over the internet. Legal status depends on the content being accessed and whether the viewer holds the appropriate licence or subscription rights for their region. Customers are responsible for their own use, and we recommend staying compliant with the content access rules that apply in your area.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Why Choose UKIPTVBOX for Your UK IPTV Subscription?',
    body: 'UKIPTVBOX gives you the full lineup on every plan, with no features held back for higher tiers. The server infrastructure is scaled before match nights, not after complaints arrive, and every WhatsApp message goes to a real person who replies in under two minutes during UK hours. No auto-renewal, and a genuine 7-day refund window if the service does not perform on your setup.',
  },
];
---
<section id="about-iptv" class="section">
  <div class="container-x">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
      <span class="eyebrow">About IPTV</span>
      <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold leading-tight">
        What Is UK IPTV and Why Are <span class="bg-grad-brand bg-clip-text text-transparent">Viewers Switching?</span>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto mt-10 md:mt-12 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-text-muted text-base leading-relaxed">
        IPTV, short for Internet Protocol Television, is how modern viewers watch live TV, sport, films and series through their broadband connection rather than via cable, satellite dish or aerial. The same technology that powers iPlayer, ITVX and Sky Glass sits underneath every IPTV service. What changes between providers is the channel depth, stream quality, server reliability and the quality of support you receive when something goes wrong.
      </p>

      {sections.map((s) => (
        <div class="mt-10">
          <h3 class="flex items-start gap-3 text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary">
            <span class="mt-1 inline-block h-6 w-[3px] rounded-sm bg-brand-light shrink-0"></span>
            <span>{s.title}</span>
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-4 pl-6 text-text-muted text-base leading-relaxed">{s.body}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
